snippet.textDisplay: Zion definitely is a fucking beast. I gotta admit I get kinda weary of all the talk and hype around him but finally seeing him play in the NBA has been awesome. The league has a crazy amount of young talent. In terms of young talent I think the Nugs might have the best young class in the league, especially if MPJ stays healthy and continues on the track he is on right now. It's a great time to be a Nugs fan and I kinda like that they don't get the hype. I sure wish Jokic would have hit that dunk on Zion last night. Hope to see those two big big big dudes battle more in the future. Zion looks like fucking goliath carved from stone... Jokic looks more like a disgruntled security guard who was carved from jello. But Jokic can still match him well with his strength and moves, especially in the post.
